<subSubSection pageNumber="460" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="460">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="460">Note:</emphasis>
The application of this name is uncertain. The Clifford, van Royen, Plukenet and Hermann elements from the protologue all appear in the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName authority="L. (1759)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1759" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Sophora" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="biflora">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="460">Sophora biflora</emphasis>
L. (1759)
</taxonomicName>
in the later account in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="460">Sp. Pl.</emphasis>
, ed. 2, 1: 534. 1762. Schelpe (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="460">Veld Fl.</emphasis>
4: 28. 1974) evidently regarded 
<specimenReference collectionCode="BM" specimenCode="357">
Herb. Clifford: 357, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Crotalaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="460">Crotalaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
3 (
<collectionCode>BM</collectionCode>
)
</specimenReference>
(a 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“fake”">&quot;fake&quot;</normalizedToken>
with flowers of a 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Crotalaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="460">Crotalaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species attached to a 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Podalyria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="460">Podalyria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) as the type of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Crotalaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="villosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="460">C. villosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, concluding that it could not be synonymous with 
<taxonomicName authority="L." authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1759" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Sophora" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="biflora">
